➡️ Promotions around weekends and peak months could further boost sales.

3. Category & Size Insights
Top Category: Classic pizzas (27% of sales, ~15K units).

Other Categories: Supreme, Veggie, and Chicken each contribute ~23–25%.

Top Size: Large pizzas dominate (46% of sales), followed by Medium (30%).
➡️ Customers prefer larger sizes, which aligns with higher revenue contribution.

4. Top & Bottom Performers
Top Revenue Pizzas: Thai Chicken, Barbecue Chicken, California Chicken, Classic Deluxe, Spicy Italian (~35–43K each).

Top Quantity Pizzas: Classic Deluxe, Barbecue Chicken, Hawaiian, Pepperoni (~2.4–2.5K each).

Bottom Revenue Pizzas: Spinach, Mediterranean, Green Garden, Brie Carre (~12–16K).
➡️ Classic and chicken-based pizzas are consistent bestsellers, while niche flavors underperform.

5. Customer Behavior
Order Timing: Friday/Saturday evenings are busiest.

Category Preference: Balanced distribution across categories, but Classic leads.

Size Preference: Strong tilt toward Large pizzas.
➡️ Customers value traditional flavors and larger portions, especially during weekends.

📈 Key Takeaways
Focus marketing on weekends and peak months (Jan, Jul).

Promote Classic & Chicken pizzas as flagship products.

Consider bundling large pizzas with sides to maximize revenue.

Reassess low-performing pizzas (Spinach, Mediterranean, Brie Carre) — either improve recipes or reduce menu clutter.
